When the COMPLETE gate keeps denying on 'worktree dirty', the culprit is often a transient gm runtime marker that the verb itself just wrote (.gm/last-dispatch-ts churns every dispatch; .gm/residual-check-fired is written by residual-scan). These belong in the gitignore managed block (git rm --cached + add to gitignore), not committed each turn. Committing them only re-dirties the tree on the next dispatch, an infinite finalize loop. Fix once by ignoring; then the scan->COMPLETE path stays clean.